name: 杰森·沃德·威廉斯
name_full: 杰森·沃德·威廉斯 Jayson Ward Williams
introduction: Jayson Ward Williams, is an American film and Television actor, born in Harrisburg,Pa. After graduating from the Harrisburg Arts Magnet, he was accepted to the prestigious Carnegie Mellon School of Drama, where he received a BFA in Acting. He can be seen recurring on the upcoming AMC Show entitled Dispatches From Elsewhere.His other credits include guest starring and supporting roles on HBO's VEEP, Manhunt:Lone Wolf, Hulu's The Looming Tower, White Collar, Law & Order, The Sopranos, NYPD Blue and the TNT movie Word of Honor. He has had a supporting roles in "The Upside" and "The Benefactor" and "21 Bridges." (2019)He has also done principal work in numerous national commercials, some of which include Verizon (with Jamie Foxx), Kraft Mac & Cheese, Burger King, Subway, Lowes, Fed-Ex, KFC and many, many more.
